<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,846,1339]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
New record for Madeira. The species appears to have been absent from Madeira until a few years ago. Since 
<number box="[223,282,1234,1260]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="2003.0">2003</number>
(if not earlier) it regularly appears in Funchal fish market (figure 
<number box="[1057,1072,1234,1260]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="7.0">7</number>
) and the fishermen state that it has been caught in Madeira waters. The first author has seen the species during a 
<collectionCode box="[1146,1244,1273,1299]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">SCUBA</collectionCode>
dive at Caniço, south-eastern coast of Madeira. 
<accessionNumber box="[526,678,1313,1339]" httpUri="http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/MMF35194" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
